Since winning The Voice Kids Germany, Mimi has grown into an artist with a powerful voice and a sound entirely her own. Blending indie pop sensibilities with deeply personal singer-songwriter storytelling, she's carved out a space that feels both contemporary and timeless.Fresh off the release of her second solo EP, Getting Older, Mimi is hitting the road for her first headline tour‚Äîand she's inviting you to be part of something special. This isn't just another concert; it's an intimate journey through the universal experience of growing up, with all its messy, beautiful, painful, and profound moments.Getting Older explores the different facets of coming of age: the relationships that shape us, the versions of ourselves we leave behind, and the wisdom we gain along the way. Standout tracks like "Cut The Ties" and the title track "Getting Older" capture these growing pains with striking honesty and emotional depth. These are songs that feel like pages from a diary‚Äîvulnerable, relatable, and deeply human.Known for crafting her songs on guitar and piano before bringing them to life in the studio, Mimi will be joined by a full band on this tour, adding movement, energy, and new dimensions to her heartfelt catalog. Expect an evening where raw emotions meet unforgettable melodies, where quiet moments build into powerful crescendos, and where every song feels like a conversation between old friends.If you love music that makes you feel seen, understood, and a little less alone in the chaos of growing up, this is a show you absolutely don't want to miss.
